  "body": "Hey team,\r\n\r\nI recently upgraded to the M1 and my compile seems to be breaking. \r\n\r\nInitially it's because theres no M1 solc build for the M1 architecture but I believe this is the work around https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/issues/2125\r\n\r\nHere is my config:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsubtask<{ solcVersion: string }>(TASK_COMPILE_SOLIDITY_GET_SOLC_BUILD, async (args, hre, runSuper) => {\r\n  if (args.solcVersion === \"0.5.17\") {\r\n    const compilerPath = path.join(__dirname, \"0.5.17+commit.d19bba13.Darwin.appleclang\");\r\n\r\n    return {\r\n      compilerPath,\r\n      isSolcJs: false, // if you are using a native compiler, set this to false\r\n      version: args.solcVersion,\r\n      // this is used as extra information in the build-info files, but other than\r\n      // that is not important\r\n      longVersion: \"0.5.17+commit.d19bba13.Darwin.appleclang\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // we just use the default subtask if the version is not 0.8.5\r\n  return runSuper();\r\n})\r\n\r\ncompilers: [\r\n      {\r\n        version: \"0.5.17\",\r\n        settings: {\r\n          optimizer: {\r\n            enabled: true,\r\n            runs: 200,\r\n          },\r\n        },\r\n      },\r\n      {\r\n        version: \"0.8.4\",\r\n        settings: {\r\n          optimizer: {\r\n            enabled: true,\r\n            runs: 200,\r\n          },\r\n        },\r\n      },\r\n    ]\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, when I try to npx hardhat comile, I run into\r\n\r\n```\r\nCompiling 38 files with 0.5.17\r\nError: write EPIPE\r\n    at WriteWrap.onWriteComplete [as oncomplete] (node:internal/stream_base_commons:98:16)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI found this issue and was wondering if it was related https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/issues/2004? I believe 0.5.0 should be supported by hardhat?\r\n\r\nThanks!",
